Hi Redblade.<br />Implemented the Trick.<br />Download the .zip file and there is bitmap- Emblem1_mask.<br />Open it with MS Paint.<br />Add the text you want in the red boxes by Using [A] Command.<br /><br /><span style="text-decoration: underline">Note1:-</span> Write With GREEN Color. I mean text should be green. By green, I mean 255 Green Value Or RGB-00FF00.<br /><br /><span style="text-decoration: underline">Note2:-</span> Try to keep labels small. Text size should not be greater than about 11. Otherwise, labels get outside from tile as well.<br /><br /><span style="text-decoration: underline">Note3:-</span> No need of old Tile Text.png and Tile Background.bmp<br /><br /><span style="text-decoration: underline">Caution1:-</span> As before, don't move boxes here and there.<br /><br /><span style="text-decoration: underline">Drawback:-</span> There is a little drawback of new trick. Alignment. You yourself have to move the textbox to right place.<br /><br />After done, load the skin file, There is option for chosing emblem mask, point to the file.<br />Other Options, Your Choices.<br />In this revision, most of the options are merged together.<br /><br /><br />Bye.<br /><br />And Yes, How I forgot about it.<br />23kb.<img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_lol.gif" alt=":lol:" title="Laughing" /><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=20364">meetHG</a> — Sat Aug 12, 2017 6:32 am</p><hr />
